 re-establishing community relationships, an integrated sense of self, and a hopeful story beyond trauma. This book vividly demonstrates that hagiographies played a vital therapeutic role in helping early Christian trauma survivors recover and flourish in the aftermath of disastrous persecutions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aCyprian. 4aErholung. 4aHagiographie. 4aPassion. 4aTrauma. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aCyprian.  aHagiography.  aPassion.  aRecovery.  aTrauma.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97815015113870 cprintz978150151890440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151126440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501511264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501511264/original  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023